00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:11.000
 Customize your Samsung Galaxy S 5 using the many customization features. Watch this video to find out how. 

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:16.000
 To add an app shortcut to your Home screen: Tap App first. 

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
 Then, touch and hold your finger on the app you want to move to your home screen. 

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:25.000
 Move the app to the Home screen and drop. 

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:31.000
 To add a widget to a Home screen: Touch and hold your finger on any empty space on your Home screen. 

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:34.000
 Then, at the bottom of the screen, tap Widgets. 

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:43.000
 Several types of widgets are available to you and some can be customized as bookmark widgets, contacts, and music list. Try them all and customize your style. 

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:46.000
 Select the Calendar Widgets option. 

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:51.000
 Then, touch and hold your finger on the calendar widget and place it on the home screen. 

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:54.000
 Move the bars to resize the widget. 

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:59.000
 When finished, tap anywhere on the Home screen to place the widget. 

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:05.000
 To remove an app widget or shortcut from your home screen: Touch and hold your finger on the widget or app. 

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:09.000
 Then move the icon to the trash and let go. 

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:14.000
 To create a folder: First, touch and hold your finger on the app you want to add to the folder. 

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:18.000
 Then move the app to Create Folder at the top of the screen. 

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:23.000
 Give your new folder a name and tap Done. 

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:31.000
 Now you can drag and drop any app shortcuts or contact cards into your folder to better organize your home screens. 

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:44.000
 With the customization of your home screens, you can also customize your favorites. Your favorites are always available, regardless of your home screen. To remove an app shortcut from your favorites: 

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:46.000
 Touch and hold your finger on the app. 

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:48.000
 Then move it out of your favorites. 

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:55.000
 You can now add any app, shortcut or folder to your favorites for quick access. 

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:57.000
 Touch and hold an icon. 

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:59.000
 Then move it to your favorites. 

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:05.000
 You can also choose your wallpaper. Touch and hold your finger on an empty space or a home screen. 

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:10.000
 Then select Wallpapers, and then touch Home Screen. 

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:12.000
 Choose from the available wallpapers. 

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:20.000
 Or choose a picture as your wallpaper, tap More pictures. 

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:23.000
 Then choose your wallpaper. 

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:30.000
 Once you have chosen your background, tap Done. 

